HEADWORD: Steapsin
<hw>Ste*ap"sin</hw> <pr>(st⟦esl⟧*⟦acr⟧p"s⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>An unorganized ferment or enzyme
present in pancreatic juice. It decomposes neutral fats into glycerin
and fatty acids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

